From e204e80bfb83ec1dd35109b4b114904d182191dc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 11:29:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] =?UTF-8?q?fix:=20resolve=209=20bugs=20=E2=80=94=20PCM?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20audio,=20WS=20accept=20order,=20useRef,=20IDOR,=20memory=20l?=
 =?UTF-8?q?eaks,=20AudioContext,=20audioop=20deprecation?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Critical:
- useTTSPlayer: replace decodeAudioData with manual PCM→Float32 AudioBuffer construction
  (decodeAudioData only accepts encoded audio; pcm_s16le raw data was silently rejected,
   meaning TTS audio never played in the browser)
- interview_ws: move websocket.accept() before auth checks; send_json before accept
  throws RuntimeError in Starlette
- InterviewRoom: change currentResponseIdRef plain object to useRef (was recreated
  on every render, losing response ID and breaking deduplication)

Security:
- interview.py/report.py/resume.py/behavior.py: add _assert_session_owner() check to
  all 8 session endpoints (IDOR — any authenticated user could access any session)
- auth.py: add periodic cleanup to _loginAttempts dict (unbounded memory growth)

Quality:
- interview_ws.py: rename inner 'payload' to 'msg_payload' to eliminate variable shadowing
- interview_ws.py: use str(session_id) key consistently in _behavior_warning_last_sent;
  clean up entry on WebSocketDisconnect to prevent memory leak
- useAudioRecorder: store AudioContext in ref and close it in stop() to release audio hardware
- report_service.py: extract _apply_report_fields() helper, eliminating ~50 duplicate lines
- sensevoice_stt_service.py: replace deprecated audioop.ratecv with pure-Python linear
  resampler (_resample_pcm_s16le) — audioop removed in Python 3.13
- main.py: add Content-Security-Policy and Referrer-Policy security headers
